ob Title: Assistant Store Manager (Job Code 1810)</p><p>Department: Store Administration (Dept. Number 901)</p><p>Reports to: Store Manager</p><p>Position Summary: The Assistant Store Manager assists in managing daily operations of an assigned store. In addition to supporting overall store operations, the Assistant Store Manager is responsible for modeling Earth Fareâs Vision, Mission, Declaration and Customer Service Creed, while training and developing a successful team.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Essential Functions</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Champion of the Earth Fare Customer Service Creed. Focuses on customer satisfaction and ensures that Team Members provide customers with superior customer service 100% of the time. (10%)</p><p>Maintains positive working relationships with direct reports, peers, supervisors, suppliers, and customers. Effectively handles complex or difficult situations involving others. Inspires, develops, trains and promotes future leaders. (15%)</p><p>Serves as a role model promoting a positive attitude and embracing the Earth Fare Declaration, Vision and Mission. Motivates Team Members to perform with excellence in their immediate job responsibilities and towards common objectives as a team. (10%)</p><p>Ensures Book of Food schematics are properly set, including creating attractive displays, merchandising new items, sales items and promotional tie-ins, in order to meet the sales and profit objectives of the store and the departments. (20%)</p><p>Forecasts, schedules, and monitors labor to be consistent with store sales and productivity guidelines and wage budgets; creates action plan to address cost control issues. (10%)</p><p>Communicates sales goals, department performance, and sales opportunities with Team Members to ensure positive results. Coordinates and oversees store inventories. (15%)</p><p>Manages issues relating to store maintenance, cleanliness/sanitation, and safety. (5%)</p><p>Partners with Store Manager in all phases of store operations to include opening and closing the store. (15%)</p><p>Total Percentage Equals 100%</p><p>HP123</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required Skills</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Knowledge and Critical Skills/Expertise</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Grocery retail leadership experience required, with Earth Fare Department Management experience preferred.</p><p>Leadership ability with a positive track record of building, motivating and inspiring others to achieve personal and professional excellence.</p><p>World class customer service skills reflecting Earth Fareâs Customer Service Creed.</p><p>Must care for people and have a keen interest and ability in developing others to become future leaders of Earth Fare.</p><p>Commitment to Earth Fareâs Vision, Mission and Declaration.</p><p>Excellent written and oral communication skills.</p><p>Professional, friendly, and approachable demeanor.</p><p>Proficient computer skills with knowledge of Microsoft Outlook, Word and Excel software. Experience using iPads and iPhones a plus.</p><p>Willingness to work a flexible schedule to include nights, weekends and holidays. Flexibility to support sister stores in the same region when business needs arise.</p><p>Desire to become a future Store Manager with the flexibility to relocate within a regional territory required. Willingness to relocation anywhere within Earth Fareâs growing footprint preferred.</p><p>Bilingual English/Spanish a plus.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required Experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Retail leadership experience with an emphasis on exceptional customer service, building strong teams, and motivating and inspiring others to be the best they can be!</p><p>Must be a strong operator and competent in understanding the interrelatedness of net sales, gross profit, shrink, labor, and and excellent ordering practices.</p><p>Perishable experience and OSHA ServSafe Certification preferred.</p><p>Leadership experience with Earth Fare preferred.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Position Type: Full Time</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/apply-for-job/biqri4/earth-store-manager-net-huntsville-al" id="ApplyBottomLink" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;ApplyForJob&#39;, &#39;BottomButton&#39;);">Apply now</a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/biqqfh/bakery-earth-pastry-baker-huntsville-al" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">Baker - Part Time &amp; Full Time</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Huntsville, AL</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - bakery, earth, pastry, baker, case, manager,...</span></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bjq9n2/general-manager-auto-motor-huntsville-al" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;1&#39;);">Automotive Store Manager</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Huntsville, AL</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - general manager, auto, manager, automotive, motor,...</span></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bithfc/jewelry-watch-brand-bridge-huntsville-al" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;2&#39;);">Store Manager - Bridge Street</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Huntsville, AL</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - jewelry, bridge, watch, fashion, brand, talent,...</span></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bjl9hi/spa-time-retail-poo